The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has shifted its Osun State Gubernatorial Screening Appeals, earlier scheduled for Jan. 19, to Monday, Jan. 24. The party disclosed this in a statement by its National Organising Secretary, Mr Umar Bature, on Tuesday night in Abuja.   PGF DG confirms resignation, says it is in APC’s best…     Fresh treason charges force shift of Nnamdi Kanu’s trial     How governors foiled plot to scuttle APC convention   The party said that the venue of the exercise remains the PDP National Secretariat, Abuja, at 10 a.m. prompt. It urged all gubernatorial aspirants and critical stakeholders of the party in Osun State to take note of the change in date and be guided accordingly. (NAN)